Step 8–Assessing the applicability domain Applicability domain measure (ADM) for the target compound is computed based on similarities between the target compound and compounds in its local group (Fig. 3). The target compound is assigned a rank between 1 and 5. The higher average similarity with compounds from the local group corresponds to the higher ADM rank. This measure can therefore be used to assess the coverage of chemical space relevant to the class of the target compound and, on the basis of the desired ADM cutoff, either to accept the final prediction as reliable or to reject it.Fig. 3
